{
  "stem": "1387.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't recall how much of what.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was also possible for my girlfriend to come out to that camp and finding me on the road shoveling snow and giving me something to eat or whatever.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My brother-in-law, who was also in the Judenrat, made arrangements some months later to transfer me to the [NON-ENGLISH], Zloczow.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was an improvement because we had already a place where to sleep-- a little more decent place to sleep.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The verkstaden, they were called-- they had artisans from all professions-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] shoemakers, furriers, clothiers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were making all kinds of things for Sturmfuhrer Warzog at the time and for his friends and for his family in Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My teacher was there painting paintings-- making paintings for, for Warzog, which he also distributed as gifts and so forth.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that-- no, I was in--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My family was transferred from Sasow to the ghetto Zloczow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That would be-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] that was in the late summer of 1942.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father passed away 25 days in the month of Adar.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That night, I [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] got out from [NON-ENGLISH] camp in Zloczow and smuggled myself into the ghetto Zloczow to say Kaddish after my father.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That same night, a Yiddish, a Jewish policeman came running to the verkstaden where we are, we were and told us that the ghetto Zloczow is surrounded by German SS, and a liquidation is taking place.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a great deal of shooting, a great deal of commotion.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the next day, around 11 o'clock, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was working in the verkstaden, selecting the clothing of the people that were killed in, in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
